nodes.title: MASK to SEGS
widgets_values:
*combined: if disabled, the mask will include any content within the boundaries of the SEGS, even if it has not been specified via GroundingDINO.

*crop_factor: multiplication factor for the size of the segment(SEGS)/boundary box(BBOX). It defines how much of the area surrounding the SEGS/BBOX should be considered during the detail recovery process. If this value is small, the restoration may not work well because the surrounding context cannot be known.

*bbox_fill: if enabled, the maks will include the content of the BBOX surrounding the SEGS.

*drop_size: any SEGS/BBOX smaller than this value will be ignored. It works in the opposite way of a guide_size value.

nodes.title: Face Detector
widgets_values:
*bbox_threshold: the confidence threshold for face recognition. If the Face Detector is identifying objects that are not faces as faces, increase this value. If the workflow is not picking up enough faces, decrease this value.

*bbox_dilation: by how much the node should expand the detected mask area.

*crop_factor: how many times the surrounding area should be included in the detail recovery process based on the detected mask area. If this value is small, the restoration may not work well because the surrounding context cannot be known. If it's too large, there will be very little upscaling done by the Detailer nodes and so less opportunity to improve the quality of the faces.

*drop_size: any segment(SEGS)/boundary box(BBOX) smaller than this value will be ignored. It works in the opposite way of a guide_size value.

nodes.title: Object Swapper
widgets_values:
*guide_size: any segment(SEGS)/boundary box(BBOX) larger than this value will be ignored. It works in the opposite way of a drop_size value. If the SEGS/BBOX is smaller than this value, the node will increase its resolution and attempt to recover details.

*guide_size_for: whether guide_size is used based on the size of the detected SEGS/BBOX or the size of the crop area that includes the face and is broadly cropped by crop_factor.

*max_size: the guide_size increases the scale so that the shorter side reaches the guide_size. For masks with elongated shapes, this can cause a significant scale up. The max_size limits the maximum size of one side.

*feather**: the thickness of the gradient used to compose the recovered details onto the original image, so that the boundaries are not visible.

*noise_mask: if enabled, denoising will not be applied outside the masked area, which can result in a safer generation with stronger denoising, but it may not always produce good results.

*force_inpaint**: force_inpaint will try to force regeneration even if it is smaller than guide_size. This function is useful when you simply want to change to another type of prompt other than the function to save details. However, in this case, upscale is forcibly fixed to 1.
    

Partially copied from: 
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-extension-tutorials/Main/ComfyUI-Impact-Pack/tutorial/advanced.md

nodes.title: Refiner Steps
widgets_values:
To change the % of steps performed by the Base SDXL model and the Refiner SDXL model, modify the value "refiner_start".

Example:

Refiner_start = 0.75 

This means 75% steps done by the Base, 25% steps done by the Refiner.


If you don't want the SDXL Refiner model to perform any step (useful when you use a fine-tuned SDXL Base model), set the "refiner_start" to 1.

nodes.title: Inpainter without Mask
widgets_values:
When you use the "Inpainter without Mask" function (aka Img2Img), be sure to disable the Refiner function, and set the "Refiner_Start" parameter to 1 in the "Controller" function. 

If you forget that, only a portion of the steps will be performed, resulting in an image that might look blurred or unfinished.

nodes.title: Denoise for inpainting w/o mask
widgets_values:
If you are doing a full inpainintg (img2img), you want the denoise value to 0.5 or lower to make minor changes, or a value of up to 0.75 for major changes.

Beyond 0.75, the generated image starts to lose any connection with the source image. To retain the resemblance, you must also activate and configure the ControlNet function.

nodes.title: System Prompt (Collage)
widgets_values:
You are a famous surrealist collage artist. I'll pass you a text that describes a subject that must be turned into a collage artwork. You need to improve the description and rephrase it as a caption.

To perform this task, identify the key elements of the description and enrich each of them by adding many details. 

For example, if I would pass the text "a yellow box sits on the table", you would identify and enrich "a yellow box", "sits", and "on the table".

Then, add some final words describing the high quality of the image.

To enrich the description and generate the caption, you must STRICTLY follow these rules:

1. You NEVER comment on the task, explain your choices, or write introductory text.

2. You NEVER output anything except your caption.

3. You ALWAYS start with "Collage art of "

4. You NEVER end the caption with a period.

Text:

widgets_values:
You are a caption generator. I'll pass you a text that describes an image. You need to improve the description and rephrase it as a caption.

To perform this task, identify the key elements of the description and enrich each of them by adding many details.

For example, if the description contains the text "a yellow box sits on the table", you would identify and enrich "a yellow box", "sits", and "on the table".

Then, add some final words describing the high quality of the image.

To enrich the description and generate the caption, you must STRICTLY follow these rules:

1. You NEVER comment on the task, explain your choices, or write introductory text.

2. You NEVER output anything except your caption.

3. You NEVER end the caption with a period.

nodes.title: Force Inpaint
widgets_values:
When "force_inpaint" is disabled, any face larger than the value defined for "guide_size" will not be detailed.

This is useful if a face is already large and detailed enough and there's no need to redraw it. 

However, if your base model generates poorly detailed faces, it's probably a good idea to force inpaint all of them.

widgets_values:
- cfg_scale

Your usual CGF parameter to control prompt adherence.

1-4: default quality 
4-7.5: high detail

- control_scale

ControlNet strength.

nodes.title: SUPIR Model Loader + Image Preparation + Encode
widgets_values: Set both the "diffusion_dtype" (in the SUPIR Model Loader node) and the "encoder_dtype" (in the SUPIR Image Preparation node) to fp32 only if you have macOS.

nodes.title: CCSR Upscaling Steps
widgets_values:
CCSR upscaling with the Gaussian Weights method (recommended) seems to yield the best out-of-the-box results at 6x and above.

For upscaling up to 4x, you can keep the "steps" value at 3 (the minimum) without observable quality degradation. 

For upscaling from 6x and above, a "steps" value of 20 is recommended.

nodes.title: SUPIR Original Demo Parameters
widgets_values:
--edm_steps: Number of steps for the EDM Sampling Scheduler. This determines how many iterations the sampling process will take. A higher number generally means more refinement but takes longer.

--s_stage1: Strength control for the first stage of processing. A negative value indicates that this stage is not used.

--s_churn: A hyperparameter of the EDM process, influencing the variability or diversity in the generated samples.

--s_noise: Another hyperparameter for EDM, affecting the amount of noise introduced during the diffusion process, which can impact the clarity or smoothness of the output.

--s_cfg: Classifier-free guidance scale for prompts. This parameter adjusts the influence of textual prompts on the generation process, affecting how closely the output matches the given textual description.

--s_stage2: Strength control for the second stage of processing. Adjusts the intensity of modifications in the second stage.

linear_CFG and --linear_s_stage2: These settings allow for a linear increase of the s_cfg and s_stage2 parameters from their start points (--spt_linear_CFG and --spt_linear_s_stage2) to their specified values through the process, providing a way to dynamically adjust the guidance strength.

--spt_linear_CFG and --spt_linear_s_stage2: Define the starting points for the linear increase of s_cfg and s_stage2, respectively.

--ae_dtype and --diff_dtype: Specify the data types (precision) used during inference for the autoencoder and diffusion processes, respectively, affecting memory usage and computational speed.

nodes.title: Cycles
widgets_values:
The number of cycles defines how many passes the detailer must perform. Increase the value if you want more detailed hands.

The Detailer starts the first cycle with the denoise value indicated above and then progressively reduces/increases the noise according to the "target_denoise" setting in the "DenoiseSchedulerDetailerHookProvider" node, on the left.

nodes.title: Hand Detailer
widgets_values:
The Hand Detailer cannot fully redraw hands because we still don't have exceptional models that can do that.

The Hand Detailer, instead, will try improve the aspect of existing hands by using the anatomy of the hand as guidance.

The Hand Detailer uses the new Mesh Graphormer method and the Inpaint Depth Hand ControlNet model.

For more information: https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.17957

nodes.title: Empty Pos Prompt for CLIP L (SD3 only)
CLIP
widgets_values:
By default, the CLIP is configured to work with SD1.5, SDXL, and SD3. 

When used with SD3, the default configuration, uses the same positive prompt for all text encoders (CLIP G, CLIP L, and T5).

If you use SD3, and you know what you are doing, you can change this configuration by:

1. Disconnecting the "CLIP Positive (SD 1/XL/3)" node and connecting the "CLIP Positive (SD3 only)" node. 

2. (optional) Define a dedicated positive prompt for T5 in the Prompt Builder function, and connect the "Get_T5_Prompt" node on the left to the ""CLIP Positive (SD3 only)" node.

Refer to the documentation at https://perilli.com/ai/comfyui/ for further information.

nodes.title: System Prompt (AI Cinema)
widgets_values:
You are an acclaimed film director. I'll pass you a text that describes a scene. You need to improve the description with all the information relevant for your crew to shoot the scene. Then, you need rephrase the improved description as a caption.


To improve the scene description and generate the caption, you must STRICTLY follow these rules:

1. You NEVER comment on the task, explain your choices, or write introductory text.

2. You NEVER output anything except your caption.

3. You MUST describe the shot in terms of type of scene, camera angle, type of camera, focus, etc.

4. If the text refers to a person, you MUST also describe his/her name, nationality, age, hair color, etc.

5. You NEVER mention "RED Komodo" as type of camera.

6. You ALWAYS start with "Cinematic film still of"

7. You NEVER end the caption with a period.

8. You MUST be very extensive in your description and use 10,000 characters.


Example 1: 

Cinematic film still of a woman looking through a window, in the style of dark tonalities, dappled, cinestill 50d, captures the essence of nature, quirky portraits, cabincore, realistic yet ethereal, movie still, photo taken with sony a7s III

Example 2:

Cinematic film still from Tropical Heist (2015) thriller in Caribbean Bermuda, gaunt young white man wearing panama hat, glistening sweat, hacking into laptop, luxury beach hotel room, low-key lighting, outstanding cinematography directed by Kathryn Bigelow, 8k HD

Example 3:

Cinematic film still, cinematic view of the surface of Jupiter's moon Europa, Ultra-detailed 30mm action cinematic sequence in the spirit of blade runner 2049 by roger deakins. Intense white fog with a bright white glow. dark Night time. Two Astro-Researchers, uncover an ancient alien monument on a Saturn moon beach. Dynamic shifting sands, cosmic horizons, extraterrestrial mysteries, hyper-maximalist, film grain, shot with Hasselblad X1D II 30mm lens, interstellar discovery, golden-ringed backdrops, metallic reflections off alien structures
